'''Hap''' was a [[Gender|male]] [[Latero]] [[bartender]] and [[chef]] who operated [[Hap's Sap Tap]] on the [[forest]] [[planet]] [[Tenoo]] during the [[High Republic Era]].<ref name="The Young Jedi" />

==Biography==
Hap lived on [[Tenoo]], where he owned a [[Cafe|café]] called [[Hap's Sap Tap]]. He was friends with young [[pilot]] [[Nash Durango]]. In [[232 BBY]], his café was repeatedly raided by a [[Taborr's gang|gang]] of [[pirate]]s. During [[Raid on Hap's Sap Tap|one of these raids]], Hap, who had heard that Durango was transporting [[Jedi]] passengers to Tenoo, contected her and asked for help. To his disappointment, the Jedi were only [[youngling]]s, but they still agreed to help him.

The three younglings, [[Kai Brightstar]], [[Lys Solay]] and [[Nubs]], confronted the pirates, but their captain, [[Cyrus Vuundir|Taborr Val Dorn]], caused a giant [[Tenoo tree|tree]] branch to fall on Hap's café. The Jedi managed to use the [[The Force|Force]] to save the café from the tree branch, and retrieved Hap's belongings from the pirates with Nash Durango's help.<ref name="The Young Jedi" />

